On Tuesday [1 March], the two leaders will begin their discussions on a wide range of issues including Russia, Bosnia, Northern Ireland and the world trade. Clinton will then share his Air Force One back to the nation's capital. Welcoming British Prime Minister John Major in Pittsburgh, where major's grandfather and father once lived, Clinton said at the airport, We're working together today to respond to the terrible tragedy in Bosnia to try to bring an end to the killing and to bring peace and to keep that conflict from spreading. 